Money Stuff =0A I think a useful rough model is something like: You and I a=
nd most people are =0Aapproximately 100% subject to the law.%20 If we do cr=
imes we=E2=80=99l =0A=0A=0A <> =0A =0A<https://sli.bloomberg.com/click=3Fs=
=3D825881&stpe=3Ddefault&li=3D12043152&m=3D21d6dea82d6b16615cf44233be620525=
&p=3D12162024>=0A=0A=0A=0AOh Gary=0A=0AI think a useful rough model is some=
thing like:=0A=0A * You and I and most people are approximately 100% subjec=
t to the law. [1]  <>=0A If we do crimes we=E2=80=99ll get arrested; if we =
commit securities violations we=E2=80=99ll =0Aget fined; if we drive too fa=
st we=E2=80=99ll get pulled over. =0A * Elon Musk is, like, 60% subject to =
the law=3F =0A * In roughly a month, he will be, like, 20% subject to the l=
aw=3F [2]  <> =0AMusk is extremely rich, he=E2=80=99s litigious and willing=
 to fight even without great =0Alegal arguments, he=E2=80=99s popular onlin=
e and has a large army of fans who get mad =0Aat his critics, and he is ess=
